# Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) Configuration
# Created: 2025-10-18
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file contents to your .env.local file
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Firebase credentials
# 3. NEVER commit .env.local to version control

# ============================================
# Frontend - Firebase SDK Configuration
# ============================================
# Get these values from Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Your apps
# https://console.firebase.google.com/project/my-detail-area/settings/general

# Your Firebase API Key
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyD... # REPLACE WITH YOUR ACTUAL API KEY

# Firebase Auth Domain (usually: your-project-id.firebaseapp.com)
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=my-detail-area.firebaseapp.com

# Firebase Project ID
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=my-detail-area

# Firebase Storage Bucket
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=my-detail-area.firebasestorage.app

# Firebase Messaging Sender ID (Cloud Messaging > Settings)
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=242154179799

# Firebase App ID
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:242154179799:web:7c5b71cdcdeedac9277492 # REPLACE WITH YOUR ACTUAL APP ID

# Firebase Measurement ID (optional - for Analytics)
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX # REPLACE IF USING ANALYTICS

# ============================================
# Backend - Supabase Edge Function Configuration
# ============================================
# Set these in Supabase Dashboard > Edge Functions > Secrets
# Or use: supabase secrets set FCM_SERVER_KEY=your_key

# Legacy FCM Server Key (Cloud Messaging > Settings > Cloud Messaging API (Legacy))
# NOTE: For production, migrate to OAuth2 with service account JSON
# FCM_SERVER_KEY=AAAA... # Set this via Supabase secrets

# FCM Project ID (same as VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID)
# FCM_PROJECT_ID=my-detail-area # Set this via Supabase secrets

# ============================================
# How to Get Your Credentials
# ============================================

# 1. Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Select project: my-detail-area
# 3. Go to: Project Settings (gear icon) > General
# 4. Scroll to: Your apps > Web apps
# 5. Copy the config object values to the VITE_ variables above

# For FCM Server Key (Edge Function):
# 1. Go to: Project Settings > Cloud Messaging
# 2. Find: "Cloud Messaging API (Legacy)" section
# 3. Copy: Server key
# 4. Set in Supabase: supabase secrets set FCM_SERVER_KEY=YOUR_KEY

# ============================================
# Testing Configuration
# ============================================

# To verify configuration is loaded correctly:
# 1. Open browser console
# 2. Run: import { getFirebaseConfigStatus } from './src/config/firebase'
# 3. Check: getFirebaseConfigStatus() - all should be true

# ============================================
# Security Notes
# ============================================

# - NEVER commit .env.local to git
# - API Key is safe for frontend (restricted by Firebase domain settings)
# - Server Key MUST be kept secret (only in Edge Functions)
# - Configure Firebase Security Rules for production
# - Use OAuth2 with service account for production (not legacy server key)
